Package: iotables
Type: Package
Title: Importing and manipulating symmetric input-output tables
Version: 0.2.0
Author: Daniel Antal, CFA
Maintainer: Daniel Antal, CFA  <daniel.antal@ceemid.eu>
Description: This package provides the necessary data 
    pre-processing tasks related to working with Eurostat's symmetric input-output
    tables and provide basic input-output economics calculations. The package is 
    a part of rOpenGov to open source open government initiatives.
URL: https://github.com/rOpenGov/iotables
BugReports: https://github.com/rOpenGov/iotables/issues
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Imports: dplyr,
    eurostat,
    magrittr,
    tidyr,
    stats,
    forcats,
    utils
Suggests: testthat,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Depends: R(>= 2.10.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
